column4: The date when the event was logged (YYYYMMDD format in the registered timezone of your app).
The name of the event.
The time (in microseconds, UTC) when the event was logged on the client.
The time (in microseconds, UTC) when the event was previously logged on the client.
The currency-converted value (in USD) of the event's "value" parameter.
The sequential ID of the bundle in which these events were uploaded.
Timestamp offset between collection time and upload time in micros.
The unique ID assigned to a user.
The pseudonymous id (e.g., app instance ID) for the user. A unique identifier that is assigned to a user when they first open the app or visit the site.
The time (in microseconds) at which the user first opened the app or visited the site.
The numeric ID of the data stream from which the event originated.
The data stream platform (Web, IOS or Android) from which the event originated.
Whether the user was active (True) or inactive (False) at any point in the calendar day. Included in only the daily tables (events_YYYYMMDD).
A number indicating the sequential order of each event within a batch based on their order of occurrence on the device.
A sequential number assigned to a page that increases for each subsequent page within an engagement.
A monotonically increasing number that is incremented each time a network request is sent from a given page.
The time (in microseconds) at which the user first opened the app or visited the site.
Whether Analytics storage is enabled for the user. Possible values: Yes, No, Unset
Whether ad targeting is enabled for a user. Possible values: Yes, No, Unset
Whether a web user has denied Analytics storage and the developer has enabled measurement without cookies based on transient tokens in server data. Possible values: Yes, No, Unset
The Lifetime Value (revenue) of the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.
The device category (mobile, tablet, desktop).
The device brand name.
The device model name.
The device marketing name.
The device model information retrieved directly from the operating system.
The operating system of the device.
The OS version.
IDFV (present only if IDFA is not collected).
Advertising ID/IDFA.
The OS language.
The device's Limit Ad Tracking setting. On iOS14+, returns false if the IDFA is non-zero.
The offset from GMT in seconds.
The browser in which the user viewed content.
The version of the browser in which the user viewed content.
The city from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The country from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The continent from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The region from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The subcontinent from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The metro from which events were reported, based on IP address.
The package name or bundle ID of the app.
The app's versionName (Android) or short bundle version.
The Firebase App ID associated with the app
The store that installed the app.
Name of the marketing campaign that first acquired the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.
Name of the medium (paid search, organic search, email, etc.) that first acquired the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.
Name of the network that first acquired the user. This field is not populated in intraday tables.
